Melt chocolate chips and margarine in a heavy pan over low heat. Remove from heat and add beaten egg slowly. Let cool 15 minutes. Gently add marshmallows and nuts. Chill in refrigerator 30 minutes. Form into a large log and roll in coconut. Wrap in waxed paper and chill several hours. Cut in slices. Variation: If in a hurry, use a 8 inch square pan . Cover bottom with coconut, add completed mixture then cover top with more coconut. Chill well then cut into small squares.